{"parse":{"title":"Latter Day Saint views on Mary","pageid":32883462,"revid":848944833,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:162px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Andrea_della_Robbia_Devotional_relief_VA_7630-1861_img01.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cf/Andrea_della_Robbia_Devotional_relief_VA_7630-1861_img01.jpg/160px-Andrea_della_Robbia_Devotional_relief_VA_7630-1861_img01.jpg\" width=\"160\" height=\"272\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cf/Andrea_della_Robbia_Devotional_relief_VA_7630-1861_img01.jpg/240px-Andrea_della_Robbia_Devotional_relief_VA_7630-1861_img01.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cf/Andrea_della_Robbia_Devotional_relief_VA_7630-1861_img01.jpg/320px-Andrea_della_Robbia_Devotional_relief_VA_7630-1861_img01.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1952\" data-file-height=\"3318\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Andrea_della_Robbia_Devotional_relief_VA_7630-1861_img01.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/wiki/Mary_(mother_of_Jesus)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mary (mother of Jesus)\">Mary</a> with <a href=\"/wiki/Jesus\" title=\"Jesus\">Jesus</a></div></div></div>\n<p>The <a href=\"/wiki/Latter_Day_Saint_movement\" title=\"Latter Day Saint movement\">Latter Day Saint movement</a>  teaches that <a href=\"/wiki/Mary_(mother_of_Jesus)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mary (mother of Jesus)\">Mary</a> was the mother of <a href=\"/wiki/Jesus\" title=\"Jesus\">Jesus</a>, whose father was <a href=\"/wiki/God_the_Father\" title=\"God the Father\">God the Father</a>. Latter Day Saints affirm the <a href=\"/wiki/Virgin_birth_of_Jesus\" title=\"Virgin birth of Jesus\">virgin birth of Jesus</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> but reject the Roman Catholic traditions of the <a href=\"/wiki/Immaculate_Conception\" title=\"Immaculate Conception\">Immaculate Conception</a>, the <a href=\"/wiki/Perpetual_virginity_of_Mary\" title=\"Perpetual virginity of Mary\">perpetual virginity of Mary</a>, and her <a href=\"/wiki/Assumption_of_Mary\" title=\"Assumption of Mary\">assumption</a>. They also believe that the <a href=\"/wiki/Brothers_of_Jesus\" title=\"Brothers of Jesus\">brothers of Jesus</a> were her and <a href=\"/wiki/Saint_Joseph\" title=\"Saint Joseph\">Joseph</a>'s biological children.<sup id=\"cite_ref-EOM_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-EOM-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Mary is not seen as an intercessor between humankind and Jesus, and Latter Day Saints do not pray to Mary.<sup id=\"cite_ref-EOM_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-EOM-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The <a href=\"/wiki/Book_of_Mormon\" title=\"Book of Mormon\">Book of Mormon</a>, part of the <a href=\"/wiki/Standard_Works\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Standard Works\">Latter Day Saint canon of scripture</a>, refers to Mary by name in prophecies of her mission,<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> and describes her as \"most beautiful and fair above all other virgins\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> and as a \"precious and chosen vessel.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In the first edition of the Book of Mormon (1830), Mary was referred to as \"the mother of God, after the manner of the flesh,\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> a reading that was changed by <a href=\"/wiki/Joseph_Smith\" title=\"Joseph Smith\">Joseph Smith</a> to \"the mother of the Son of God\" in subsequent editions (1837\u2013).<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Latter Day Saints also believe that God the Father is the literal father of Jesus Christ,<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> although how Jesus' conception was accomplished has not been authoritatively established.<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Latter_Day_Saint_views_on_Mary&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFColton1992\" class=\"citation\">Colton, Eleanor (1992), <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://contentdm.lib.byu.edu/cdm/ref/collection/EoM/id/4311\">\"Virgin Birth\"</a>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Encyclopedia_of_Mormonism\" title=\"Encyclopedia of Mormonism\">Encyclopedia of Mormonism</a></i>, <b>4</b>, New York, NY: Macmillan Publishing Co., p.&#160;1510</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Virgin+Birth&amp;rft.btitle=Encyclopedia+of+Mormonism&amp;rft.place=New+York%2C+NY&amp;rft.pages=1510&amp;rft.pub=Macmillan+Publishing+Co.&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.aulast=Colton&amp;rft.aufirst=Eleanor&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fcontentdm.lib.byu.edu%2Fcdm%2Fref%2Fcollection%2FEoM%2Fid%2F4311&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALatter+Day+Saint+views+on+Mary\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-EOM-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-EOM_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-EOM_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFFronk1992\" class=\"citation\">Fronk, Camille (1992), <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://contentdm.lib.byu.edu/cdm/ref/collection/EoM/id/3906\">\"Mary, Mother of Jesus\"</a>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Encyclopedia_of_Mormonism\" title=\"Encyclopedia of Mormonism\">Encyclopedia of Mormonism</a></i>, <b>2</b>, New York, NY: Macmillan Publishing Co., pp.&#160;863\u201364</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Mary%2C+Mother+of+Jesus&amp;rft.btitle=Encyclopedia+of+Mormonism&amp;rft.place=New+York%2C+NY&amp;rft.pages=863-64&amp;rft.pub=Macmillan+Publishing+Co.&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.aulast=Fronk&amp;rft.aufirst=Camille&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fcontentdm.lib.byu.edu%2Fcdm%2Fref%2Fcollection%2FEoM%2Fid%2F3906&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALatter+Day+Saint+views+on+Mary\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><span class=\"plainlinks\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/3.8?lang=eng#7\">Mosiah 3&#58;8</a></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><span class=\"plainlinks\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/11.13-20?lang=eng#12\">1 Nephi 11&#58;13\u201320</a></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><span class=\"plainlinks\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/7.10?lang=eng#9\">Alma 7&#58;10</a></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation\"><i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Book_of_Mormon\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The Book of Mormon\">The Book of Mormon</a></i>, Palmyra, NY: E.B. Grandin, 1830, p.&#160;25</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Book+of+Mormon&amp;rft.place=Palmyra%2C+NY&amp;rft.pages=25&amp;rft.pub=E.B.+Grandin&amp;rft.date=1830&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALatter+Day+Saint+views+on+Mary\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.inephi.com/25.htm\">Online reprint</a> at <i>inephi.com</i> by John Hajicek.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"> <span class=\"plainlinks\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/11.18?lang=eng#17\">1 Nephi 11&#58;18</a></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Latter Day Saint author <a href=\"/wiki/Hugh_Nibley\" title=\"Hugh Nibley\">Hugh Nibley</a> has argued that the change was made to \"avoid confusion, since during the theological controversies of the early Middle Ages the expression 'mother of God' took on a special connotation which it still has for many Christians\". (<cite class=\"citation\">\"<span style=\"padding-left:0.2em;\">'</span>There Can Be No More Bible<span style=\"padding-right:0.2em;\">'</span>\", <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://maxwellinstitute.byu.edu/publications/books/?bookid=74&amp;chapid=909\"><i>Since Cumorah</i></a> (2nd ed.), Salt Lake City, UT: <a href=\"/wiki/Deseret_Book\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Deseret Book\">Deseret Book</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/FARMS\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"FARMS\">FARMS</a>, 1988 [1967], p.&#160;6, <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-87579-139-5\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-87579-139-5\">0-87579-139-5</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/OCLC\" title=\"OCLC\">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.worldcat.org/oclc/17618853\">17618853</a></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=%27There+Can+Be+No+More+Bible%27&amp;rft.btitle=Since+Cumorah&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+UT&amp;rft.pages=6&amp;rft.edition=2nd&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+Book+and+FARMS&amp;rft.date=1988&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F17618853&amp;rft.isbn=0-87579-139-5&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fmaxwellinstitute.byu.edu%2Fpublications%2Fbooks%2F%3Fbookid%3D74%26chapid%3D909&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALatter+Day+Saint+views+on+Mary\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span>)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.lds.org/manual/gospel-principles/chapter-11-the-life-of-christ?lang=eng\">\"Chapter 11: The Life of Christ\"</a>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Gospel_Principles\" title=\"Gospel Principles\">Gospel Principles</a></i>, Salt Lake City, UT: LDS Church, 2009, p.&#160;52\u201353</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp